label.value: assembler or fabricator, all other

definition.value: All assemblers and fabricators not listed separately.

label.value: food processing worker
baker (broad)
baker

definition.value: Mix and bake ingredients to produce breads, rolls, cookies, cakes, pies, pastries, or other baked goods.

label.value: butcher or other meat, poultry, or fish processing worker
butcher or meat cutter

definition.value: Cut, trim, or prepare consumer-sized portions of meat for use or sale in retail establishments.

label.value: meat, poultry, or fish cutter or trimmer

definition.value: Use hands or hand tools to perform routine cutting and trimming of meat, poultry, and seafood.

label.value: slaughterer or meat packer

definition.value: Perform nonroutine or precision functions involving the preparation of large portions of meat. Work may include specialized slaughtering tasks, cutting standard or premium cuts of meat for marketing, making sausage, or wrapping meats. Work typically occurs in slaughtering, meat packing, or wholesale establishments.

label.value: miscellaneous food processing worker
food or tobacco roasting, baking, or drying machine operator or tender

definition.value: Operate or tend food or tobacco roasting, baking, or drying equipment, including hearth ovens, kiln driers, roasters, char kilns, and vacuum drying equipment.

label.value: food batchmaker

definition.value: Set up and operate equipment that mixes or blends ingredients used in the manufacturing of food products. Includes candy makers and cheese makers.

label.value: food cooking machine operator or tender

definition.value: Operate or tend cooking equipment, such as steam cooking vats, deep fry cookers, pressure cookers, kettles, and boilers, to prepare food products.

label.value: food processing worker, all other

definition.value: All food processing workers not listed separately.

label.value: metal worker or plastic worker
forming machine setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic
extruding or drawing machine setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend machines to extrude or draw thermoplastic or metal materials into tubes, rods, hoses, wire, bars, or structural shapes.

label.value: forging machine setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend forging machines to taper, shape, or form metal or plastic parts.

label.value: rolling machine setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend machines to roll steel or plastic forming bends, beads, knurls, rolls, or plate, or to flatten, temper, or reduce gauge of material.

label.value: machine tool cutting setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic
cutting, punching, or press machine setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend machines to saw, cut, shear, slit, punch, crimp, notch, bend, or straighten metal or plastic material.

label.value: drilling or boring machine tool setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend drilling machines to drill, bore, ream, mill, or countersink metal or plastic work pieces.

label.value: grinding, lapping, polishing, or buffing machine tool setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend grinding and related tools that remove excess material or burrs from surfaces, sharpen edges or corners, or buff, hone, or polish metal or plastic work pieces.

label.value: lathe or turning machine tool setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend lathe and turning machines to turn, bore, thread, form, or face metal or plastic materials, such as wire, rod, or bar stock.

label.value: milling or planing machine setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend milling or planing machines to mill, plane, shape, groove, or profile metal or plastic work pieces.

label.value: machinist (broad)
machinist

definition.value: Set up and operate a variety of machine tools to produce precision parts and instruments out of metal. Includes precision instrument makers who fabricate, modify, or repair mechanical instruments. May also fabricate and modify parts to make or repair machine tools or maintain industrial machines, applying knowledge of mechanics, mathematics, metal properties, layout, and machining procedures.

label.value: metal furnace operator, tender, pourer, or caster
metal-refining furnace operator or tender

definition.value: Operate or tend furnaces, such as gas, oil, coal, electric-arc or electric induction, open-hearth, or oxygen furnaces, to melt and refine metal before casting or to produce specified types of steel.

label.value: pourer or caster, metal

definition.value: Operate hand-controlled mechanisms to pour and regulate the flow of molten metal into molds to produce castings or ingots.

label.value: model maker or patternmaker, metal or plastic
model maker, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up and operate machines, such as lathes, milling and engraving machines, and jig borers to make working models of metal or plastic objects. Includes template makers.

label.value: patternmaker, metal or plastic

definition.value: Lay out, machine, fit, and assemble castings and parts to metal or plastic foundry patterns, core boxes, or match plates.

label.value: molder or molding machine setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic
foundry mold or coremaker

definition.value: Make or form wax or sand cores or molds used in the production of metal castings in foundries.

label.value: molding, coremaking, or casting machine setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend metal or plastic molding, casting, or coremaking machines to mold or cast metal or thermoplastic parts or products.

label.value: multiple machine tool setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic (broad)
multiple machine tool setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend more than one type of cutting or forming machine tool or robot.

label.value: tool or die maker (broad)
tool or die maker

definition.value: Analyze specifications, lay out metal stock, set up and operate machine tools, and fit and assemble parts to make and repair dies, cutting tools, jigs, fixtures, gauges, and machinists' hand tools.

label.value: welding, soldering, or brazing worker
welder, cutter, solderer, or brazer

definition.value: Use hand-welding, flame-cutting, hand-soldering, or brazing equipment to weld or join metal components or to fill holes, indentations, or seams of fabricated metal products.

label.value: welding, soldering, or brazing machine setter, operator, or tender

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend welding, soldering, or brazing machines or robots that weld, braze, solder, or heat treat metal products, components, or assemblies. Includes workers who operate laser cutters or laser-beam machines.

label.value: miscellaneous metal worker or plastic worker
heat treating equipment setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend heating equipment, such as heat-treating furnaces, flame-hardening machines, induction machines, soaking pits, or vacuum equipment to temper, harden, anneal, or heat treat metal or plastic objects.

label.value: layout worker, metal or plastic

definition.value: Lay out reference points and dimensions on metal or plastic stock or workpieces, such as sheets, plates, tubes, structural shapes, castings, or machine parts, for further processing. Includes shipfitters.

label.value: plating machine setter, operator, or tender, metal or plastic

definition.value: Set up, operate, or tend plating machines to coat metal or plastic products with chromium, zinc, copper, cadmium, nickel, or other metal to protect or decorate surfaces. Typically, the product being coated is immersed in molten metal or an electrolytic solution.

label.value: tool grinder, filer, or sharpener

definition.value: Perform precision smoothing, sharpening, polishing, or grinding of metal objects.

label.value: metal worker or plastic worker, all other

definition.value: All metal workers and plastic workers not listed separately.

label.value: printing worker (minor)
printing worker
